@startuml backoffice-dynamodb-domain-model
title Modelo de Domínio DynamoDB do Backoffice

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype polyline
skinparam nodesep 95
skinparam ranksep 75
top to bottom direction

class "User\nBO_Users" as User {
  +userId
  +cognitoSub
  +email
  +roleIds[]
  +status
}

class "Role\nBO_Roles" as Role {
  +roleId
  +name
  +application
  +permissions[]
  +status
}

class "Permission\nBO_Permissions" as Permission {
  +id
  +name
  +application
  +category
  +status
}

class "PageGate\nBO_PageGates" as PageGate {
  +gateId
  +pageKey
  +application
  +requiredPermissions[]
}

class "AuditLog\nBO_Logs" as AuditLog {
  +logId
  +adminUserId
  +adminEmail
  +action
  +targetType
  +targetId
  +timestamp
}

User "1" -right-> "0..*" Role : roleIds
Role "1" -right-> "0..*" Permission : permissions
PageGate "*" -up-> "0..*" Permission : requiredPermissions
AuditLog "*" -up-> "1" User : adminUserId

note bottom
O DynamoDB guarda apenas o domínio administrativo
do backoffice: operadores, perfis, permissões,
page gates e auditoria.

As entidades operacionais da JustCauses
permanecem fora deste modelo.
end note

@enduml
